                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180114-110-off587 t18180114-110-crimeloc590"></join>. I keep an open shop. On the 17th of December, about eight o'clock in the morning, I was up stairs; when I came down I missed the glass off a chest of drawers.</p>
               <p>SAMUEL FURZEMAN. I am an officer. On the 17th of December I met the prisoner running up Drury-lane with the glass - I stopped him, he said he found it - He afterwards said he did it through distress.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I beg for mercy.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 21.</p>
